      "author": "martinowong",
      "description": "Section Writing Stats 1.0 is the first stable release under the plugin's clearer new name. It adds command-palette actions for creating, editing, and removing whole-note or current-section writing targets, while preserving the existing plugin ID and all saved settings for a seamless update.\n\nThe optional mobile current-section meter remains Beta. It is now more compact and follows the section visible in the editor more promptly.\n\n### Highlights\n\n- Renamed Section Meter to Section Writing Stats.\n- Added commands to set, edit, and remove writing targets without manually entering `Target:` syntax.\n- Kept live word counts, character counts, reading-time estimates, and target progress beside headings, note titles, and in the status bar.\n- Improved the optional Beta mobile meter.\n- Preserved the stable `section-meter` ID so existing installations update normally.\n",
      "downloadCount": 12,
      "draft": false,
      "name": "Section Writing Stats 1.0.0",
      "prerelease": false,
      "publishedAt": "2026-07-14T21:02:52Z",
